I am an Assistant Professor in the Department of Statistics at the University of Florida. My research interests are in multivariate analysis, numerical optimization, tensor-valued data analysis, and more generally, statistical and machine learning. I am also interested in applications in statistical genetics and genomics. To discuss collaborations, potential student projects, or matters related to coursework, please visit my office (202 Griffin-Floyd) or contact me by email (amolstad@ufl.edu).


Recent and upcoming talks:
  • December 14, 2019: Conf. on Computational and Methodological Statistics, in London, UK.
  • May 30, 2019: Symposium on Data Science and Statistics, in Bellevue, WA.
  • April 4, 2019: Seminar, Department of Biostatistics, University of Washington, in Seattle WA.
